This paper deals with meta-programming, which is a topic closely related to programming languages (cs.PL) and logic programming (cs.LO). The methodology presented in the paper is focused on termination analysis, which is a common problem in software engineering (cs.SE) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper also mentions proof trees, which are related to formal methods and logic (cs.FL).
